"Nitrogen, phosphorus and sulfur utilization by fungi"

"Nitrogen, phosphorus and sulfur are the major mineral nutrient elements in the biosphere and fungi play an essential role in their release from organic residues in terrestrial ecosystems, thus influencing plant nutrition and primary productivity. This book covers four basic areas: the physiology and metabolism of nitrogen, phosphorus and sulfur in fungi
 the role of these minerals in pathogenic relationships with plants
